author: USA TODAY, Ian Richardson, USA TODAY
title: Fact check: Early studies show pink eye could be related to COVID-19 but in few cases
description: Available research points to pink eye-related symptoms occurring rarely in COVID-19 patients, potentially only in 1% or fewer.
content:
As the COVID-19 pandemic continues, Americans wonder if the illnesses they had earlier this year were actually a result of the novel coronavirus.
